As from you question **lexicographic sort and radix sort** differences are-

**Radix Sort** is a linear sorting algorithm that sorts elements by processing them digit by digit.

    for example to sort array [ 110,22,31 ]  using Redix Sort -  
    
    So first we will arrange based on unit place-
    [110,31,22]
    Then we arrange based on 10th place-
    [110,22,31]
    Then we arrange based on 100th place-
    [22,31,110]

    Finally we have the sorted result [22,31,110].

**lexicographical Sort** is basically a dictionary order or we can say a generalization of the alphabetical order.

    for example if we want to sort the below array-
    [10,2,10001,1011,25,20001]
    
    so the lexical sort will look like-
    [10,10001,1011,2,20001,25]

Second thing you want to sort lexicographically using tree

So here we can use a **binary search tree** for that,
I am share a code for that hope it is helpful.

    public class Node {
        private int value;
       private Node left, right;
    
        public Node(int value)
        {
            this.value = value;
            left = right = null;
        }
    
        public int getValue() {
            return value;
        }
    
        public void setValue(int value) {
            this.value = value;
        }
    
        public Node getLeft() {
            return left;
        }
    
        public void setLeft(Node left) {
